cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.CR, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the detection of hidden paid posters on the Internet, which is a social phenomenon. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves the analysis of online behavior and the design of a detection mechanism, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses real-world trace data and semantic analysis, which could be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
